Introduction

ToTh6y is a five-member co-ed project group under MyDoll Entertainment consisting of members from PinkFantasy and TMC.

On April 2, 2024, former PinkFantasy member Daewang announced that she will be producing a unit group focusing on 'queer liberation'.

On May 10, 2024, the lineup of ToTh6y was revealed to be comprised of Momoka, Arang, Miku, Wonsik, and Seunghyuk.

Their group name, ToTh6y stands for "To. Theyüè≥Ô∏è‚Äçüåà", which means they want to send a message to everyone, and "Today" which stands for "Let's be happy together today". The "6" in their name is for the five members and the fans.

They will make their official debut date on November 12, 2024, but they will hold their first Japan live on July 23, 2024.
